  <h1 style="text-align: center; color: #FDB927" id="title">Kobe Bryant</h1>
  <p id="quote">"These young guys are playing checkers. I'm out there playing chess." </p>
  <figure id="img-div">
    <img id="image" src="https://weraveyou.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/kobe-1.jpg" alt="Kobe Bryant">
    <figcaption id="img-caption">
      Kobe Bryant, a former NBA superstar who spent 20 years with the Los Angeles Lakers. <figcaption>
  </figure>

  <section id="tribute-info">
    <h2 id="headline"> <u>Here's a timeline of Kobe Bryant's life:</u></h2>
    <ul>
      <li> <strong> 1978: </strong> Kobe is born in Philadelphia. His parents named him after the famous kobe beef from Japan.</li>
      <li> <strong> 1996:</strong> becomes the first guard drafted directly out of high school, selected 13th overall by the Charlotte Hornets before being quickly traded to the Los Angeles Lakers. </li>
      <li><strong> 1997:</strong> During his rookie season, Kobe becomes the youngest player to ever win the Slam Dunk Contest at All Star Weekend.</li>
      <li><strong> 1998:</strong> Kobe makes his first of 18 total All Star appearances. </li>
      <li><strong> 1999-2002: </strong> Kobe alongside Shaquille O'Neal leads the Lakers to three consecutive championships. In 2002, Kobe is named to the first of 11 All-NBA first teams. </li>
      <li><strong> 2003: </strong> Arrested in Colorado on allegations of sexual assault. The charges were dropped 14 months later.</li>
      <li><strong> 2006:</strong> Kobe scores a career high of 81 points against the Toronto Raptors, the second most points scored in a single NBA game in history.</li>
      <li><strong> 2008:</strong> Kobe is awarded NBA MVP.</li><strong> 2009-2010:</strong> Kobe led the Lakers to two more championships, winning finals MVP both years.</li>
      <li><strong> 2012:</strong> Kobe becomes the youngest player to reach 30,000 career points at age 34.</li>
      <li><strong> 2016:</strong> After a couple injury plagued years, Kobe scores 60 points against the Jazz in his final game before retirement. He finished with a career total of 33,643 points, the third most at the time.</li>
      <li><strong> 2020:</strong> On Jan. 26, the day after Lebron James surpassed Kobe on the all time scoring list, Kobe died in a tragic helicopter crash with eight others, including his daughter Gianna, at the age of 41.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3> Read more at <a id="tribute-link" target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kobe_Bryant">Wikipedia</a></h3>
  </section>
